        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 12:50PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 1249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking  strong thunderstorms in
the northern and northeastern Kansas City Metro Area, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kansas City, Liberty, Excelsior Springs, Smithville, Kearney, Lawson,
Pleasant Valley, Orrick, Glenaire, Crystal Lakes, Sibley, Missouri
City, Excelsior Estates, Levasy, Woods Heights, Rayville, Napoleon,
Mosby, Homestead, and Fleming.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 in Missouri between mile markers 15 and 31.
Interstate 435 between mile markers 41 and 49.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
